1 Data Preparation

Read in data

This data is a selection of the larger dataframe because it control for variables that show high multicollinearity

#read in data
data <- read.csv(file = 'num_perfect_rhymes_lemma_token_w_nlp.csv') %>% 
  dplyr::select(BT_easiness, SUBTLEXus_Freq_CW_Log,  rhymes_1000_coca_final_lemma, OG_N_CW, rhymes_2500_coca_final_tokens, rhymes_10000_coca_final_lemma, Freq_N_PH_CW)

Break into training and test sets

set.seed(1234)

dt = sort(sample(nrow(data_source), nrow(data_source)*.7))
train<-data_source[dt,]
test<-data_source[-dt,]
